&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dhcp-server shared-network-name LAN subnet 10.1.1.0/24 dns-server 9.9.9.9
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dhcp-server shared-network-name LAN subnet 10.1.1.0/24 lease &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;86400&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dhcp-server shared-network-name LAN subnet 10.1.1.0/24 range &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; start 10.1.1.100
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dhcp-server shared-network-name LAN subnet 10.1.1.0/24 range &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; stop 10.1.1.200
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dhcp-server shared-network-name LAN description &lt;span class=&#34;s1&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;DHCP LAN IPv4&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;commit
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Configure a DHCP Server IPv6:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dhcpv6-server shared-network-name LAN subnet 3fb7::/64 address-range start 3fb7::10 stop 3fb7::100
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dhcpv6-server shared-network-name LAN subnet 3fb7::/64 name-server 3fb7::1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;commit
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# And a DNS forwarder:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dns forwarding cache-size &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dns forwarding allow-from 10.1.1.0/24
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dns forwarding listen-address 10.1.1.1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dns forwarding name-server 1.1.1.1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; service dns forwarding name-server 9.9.9.9
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Apply and save&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;commit
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;save
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add a set of firewall policies for our &amp;ldquo;Outside&amp;rdquo; interface:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;set firewall name OUTSIDE-IN default-action &amp;lsquo;drop&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-IN rule 10 action &amp;lsquo;accept&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-IN rule 10 state established &amp;rsquo;enable&#39;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-IN rule 10 state related &amp;rsquo;enable&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL default-action &amp;lsquo;drop&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 10 action &amp;lsquo;accept&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 10 state established &amp;rsquo;enable&#39;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 10 state related &amp;rsquo;enable&#39;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 20 action &amp;lsquo;accept&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 20 icmp type-name &amp;rsquo;echo-request&#39;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 20 protocol &amp;lsquo;icmp&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 20 state new &amp;rsquo;enable&#39;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 30 action &amp;lsquo;drop&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 30 destination port &amp;lsquo;22&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 30 protocol &amp;rsquo;tcp&#39;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 30 recent count &amp;lsquo;4&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 30 recent time &amp;lsquo;60&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 30 state new &amp;rsquo;enable&#39;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 31 action &amp;lsquo;accept&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 31 destination port &amp;lsquo;22&amp;rsquo;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 31 protocol &amp;rsquo;tcp&#39;
set firewall name OUTSIDE-LOCAL rule 31 state new &amp;rsquo;enable&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply the firewall policies:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;set interfaces ethernet eth0 firewall in name &amp;lsquo;OUTSIDE-IN&amp;rsquo;
set interfaces ethernet eth0 firewall local name &amp;lsquo;OUTSIDE-LOCAL&amp;rsquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once suricata is installed and inspecting nfqueue 0 (-q 0), you can send packet to it by passing the action “inspect” to a firewall rule:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;set firewall name FROM-INTERNET default-action drop
set firewall name FROM-INTERNET description “From Internet”
set firewall name FROM-INTERNET rule 10 description “Pass port 22 traffic to Suricata”
set firewall name FROM-INTERNET rule 10 action inspect
set firewall name FROM-INTERNET rule 10 protocol tcp
set firewall name FROM-INTERNET rule 10 destination port ssh&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and this will send packets to nfqueue 0&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
